uima.cas.Sofa.sofaString: INDICATION: ___-year-old woman with a smoking history, DOE, productive cough and wheezing, found to have rales at the left lung base on exam. The lungs are hyper-expanded with associated flattening of the diaphragms. Unexplained mild rightward deviation of the trachea without tracheal narrowing at the level of the thoracic inlet, not markedly changed since ___. The lungs are otherwise clear without focal consolidation or pulmonary edema. No focal consolidation to suggest active infection. Stable unexplained mild rightward deviation of the trachea.
